3543,PullRequestEvent,2017-12-10 13:58:17+00:00,69090889,hardbyte/python-can,3647996,christiansandberg,,,133765879,,Remote protocol update,closed,False,174,"The remote interface has been a bit of a learning experience for me. It made sense to make it very low level to make it efficient, but the thought of implementing this over again in some other language made me reconsider. So I've decided to reimplement everything using WebSocket and JSON instead.

A nice side-effect of this is that I could also implement a basic web interface for simple monitoring of CAN traffic using a browser. This could be improved in the future but it's a start. I implemented a JavaScript package on [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/package/python-can-remote) that can be re-used.

Sending data using JSON will of course cause quite a bit of overhead so I added support for sending CAN messages in binary format which could be useful on busy CAN-FD buses for example.

Unfortunately I had a hard time finding a WebSocket library that implemented both the server and client side and worked in Python 2 and 3. So I decided to roll my own minimal WebSocket implementation for now.",https://api.github.com/repos/hardbyte/python-can/issues/174,,2017-12-10T13:58:17Z,2017-12-10T13:58:17Z,4,1487,1000,27,COLLABORATOR,[],"[{'login': 'hardbyte', 'id': 855189, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/855189?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hardbyte', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/hardbyte', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hardbyte/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hardbyte/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hardbyte/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hardbyte/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hardbyte/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hardbyte/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hardbyte/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hardbyte/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/hardbyte/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",[],,,,,[],https://github.com/hardbyte/python-can/pull/174.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/hardbyte/python-can/pulls/174/commits,010,"['019aeabd71f8b78ea14aad59da8173ac578076ce', '119e7e14fbca278a4dda04c61e818373bb8f6d0b', 'd55e9003a0d0c1928364faf11a3ad654c01332a2', '8eaf4abaf9e4a6a1ad6154067707febc3b669dd4']"
