3624,PullRequestEvent,2016-12-08 15:43:49+00:00,33601400,klen/aioauth-client,973454,arthurdarcet,,,97145697,,yarl is not escaping / in the query string anymore,open,False,26,"Yarl (the quoting lib used by aiohttp) does not encode the `/` in the query parameters in its latest version.
This makes the OAuth1 signatures wrong, and the TwitterClient doesn't work with the latest aiohttp version (which requires yarl 0.8.1)

I have updated the OAuth1Client to parse the url the same way aiohttp does, this should make thing a bit more reliable. (aiohttp does not expose a way to prepare a request without sending it as far as I can see, so I had to call `yarl.URL` directly).


(the second commit is a quick fix to correctly close the requests when an error occurs)",https://api.github.com/repos/klen/aioauth-client/issues/26,,,2016-12-08T15:43:49Z,2,16,15,2,[],[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/klen/aioauth-client/pull/26.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/klen/aioauth-client/pulls/26/commits,010,"['0f72c165f607c44033f9bf4181bf775ad16163fa', '678b6f9d9ec25d4bc0000c14c922998631a1892d']"
