4276,PullRequestEvent,2016-12-28 19:19:49+00:00,61503927,ssanderson/interface,1588357,ssanderson,,,99580379,,ENH: Add property as a supported type.,closed,False,3,"Enables definitions such as:

```
class FooInterface(Interface):

    @property
    def bar(self):
        pass

class Foo(implements(FooInterface)):

    @property
    def bar(self):
        return 'baz'
```

If the implementation is missing the `property` decorator, such as:

```
class FooInterface(Interface):

    @property
    def bar(self):
        pass

class Foo(implements(FooInterface)):

    def bar(self):
        return 'baz'
```

Then an error is raised showing that the method has the wrong type:

```
The following methods of FooInterface were implemented with incorrect types:
  - bar: 'function' is not a subtype of expected type 'property'
```",https://api.github.com/repos/ssanderson/interface/issues/3,2016-12-28T19:19:48Z,2016-12-28T19:19:48Z,2016-12-28T19:19:48Z,1,64,0,2,[],[],[],[],ssanderson,1588357.0,User,False,[],https://github.com/ssanderson/interface/pull/3.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/ssanderson/interface/pulls/3/commits,010,['20aa7ab2b5f0b103a7075bf03d7b70995dbe5d83']
