7802,PullRequestEvent,2018-01-20 04:41:44+00:00,18422074,venmo/business-rules,16383201,varshaAwaazDe,256998.0,venmo,164110670,,Issue with using multiple rules together with 'any' type of condition,closed,False,42,"When adding multiple rules with 'any' type, an issue was observed in the 'non_satisfy_values_to_return' returned by 'check_conditions_recursively' method of engine.py. Since we dont take a deep copy of 'non_satisfy_values_to_return' in temp before iterating, it modified the temp variable along with 'non_satisfy_values_to_return' leading issue in the loop around temp variable. 

Also the loop in method 'check_conditions_recursively' which looks like 

        temp = non_satisfy_values_to_return[:]
        for s in temp:
            if s['id'] in satisfy_values_to_return_ids:
                non_satisfy_values_to_return.remove(s)

can be simplified to look like 

        non_satisfy_values_to_return = filter(lambda non_satisfy_value:
                                              non_satisfy_value['id'] not in satisfy_values_to_return_ids,
                                              non_satisfy_values_to_return)",https://api.github.com/repos/venmo/business-rules/issues/42,,2018-01-20T04:41:44Z,2018-01-20T04:41:44Z,13,1248,274,12,NONE,[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/venmo/business-rules/pull/42.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/venmo/business-rules/pulls/42/commits,010,"['0b99d2f5a790ce1ed0895b60e5d5874df8beee45', '59dbfa6b68be11f5de68d905d29ac7dfec94936e', '91ec9e26436efc7946ed64887d9753a6e614fa3b', '5ee513a35b0d4cc81520c5d49dbe0e68936e9116', '2c4b1f0baded801141cbcfbe7fb3eb0aa165c16e', '83cc8bb7a066bd7ef313fada5b352bca62813f0c', '0e95e9d6779102a301184cbe80e44d5cafe010ac', 'f4e6b80d6353e90018ee73063fd4b9833008c8d5', '5afc59d099d75a4310f7a5ebcb8435b30889cd17', 'bf88dd0f6b6a157e19d297e881eb83739e00ec6d', '081fa0adf5a7a35d45edf9796ef1c4f56c42986c', '47404b3c71099063890947c70903cf32cb9f4ded', 'a54efb707a817209a02a889c2b911fb790005bca']"
