7815,PullRequestEvent,2018-01-03 23:27:18+00:00,648332,assimp/assimp,2323156,kimkulling,265533.0,assimp,160954247,,Bug fixes for IFC,closed,False,1676,"2 differents bug fixes for IFC files:
- Support for optional parameter not defined in IfcSIUnit
- Fix for SwepDiskSolid tessellation when using polylines with only 2 points. The proposed fix increase the reliability of the tesselation and increase the performance by avoiding redundant calls to EstimateSampleCount method.",https://api.github.com/repos/assimp/assimp/issues/1676,2018-01-03T23:27:18Z,2018-01-03T23:27:18Z,2018-01-03T23:27:18Z,3,6,5,2,CONTRIBUTOR,[],[],[],kimkulling,2323156.0,User,False,[],https://github.com/assimp/assimp/pull/1676.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/assimp/assimp/pulls/1676/commits,010,"['32dfd423dbf6487e7308969f241ffdda38f31adb', '712a7ee779da81c3331071af918a841f72ee450d', 'd0bee866c05f727c2a4d178e383c1ddadb826e4b']"
7819,PullRequestEvent,2016-02-18 10:53:57+00:00,648332,assimp/assimp,908209,acgessler,265533.0,assimp,58970870,,use NormalizeSafe to prevent NaN when normalizing zero vectors,closed,False,790,"This started here #485 and was partially fixed here #713, but I've just found one more place that needs attention for the same reason: `SmoothingGroups.inl`, which is used by 3DS loader and maybe by some other code, as well.

The problem is absolutely the same: the code computes some normals, sums them up and then normalizes, but in some cases the sum is zero, so normalization a zero vector gives unpredictable results.

That's why we've added `NormalizeSafe` and the one-line patch switches from the unsafe `Normalize` to a safer `NormalizeSafe()`.",https://api.github.com/repos/assimp/assimp/issues/790,2016-02-18T10:53:57Z,2016-02-18T10:53:57Z,2016-02-18T10:53:57Z,1,1,1,1,[],[],[],[],acgessler,908209.0,User,False,[],https://github.com/assimp/assimp/pull/790.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/assimp/assimp/pulls/790/commits,010,['4d5df6dc9a220ba4754ac1ee0ed04afd7f7402fd']
