7869,PullRequestEvent,2017-04-12 04:03:39+00:00,76404566,cloudflare/sqlalchemy-clickhouse,25078176,lu828,314135.0,cloudflare,115459985,,fix issue occurred when inheriting parent attributes,open,False,2,"I have met this issue: ""AttributeError: 'Connection' object has no attribute 'readonly'"" when query tables names. So I have analyzed your source. Based on my analysis of it, I have found one issue.
'Connection' class is inherited from Database but it does not inherit parent's method or attributes from Database class.
To fix it, I have added a following code.
```sh
super(Connection, self).__init__(db_name, db_url, username, password)
```
After that, it works for me well.",https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/sqlalchemy-clickhouse/issues/2,,,2017-04-12T04:03:39Z,1,1,0,1,[],[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/cloudflare/sqlalchemy-clickhouse/pull/2.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/cloudflare/sqlalchemy-clickhouse/pulls/2/commits,010,['6a7bb4ddb466e2c8c6779a6eb2210e80dfd80825']
