8228,PullRequestEvent,2015-04-16 07:13:26+00:00,1126087,gitpython-developers/GitPython,63622,Byron,503709.0,gitpython-developers,33379167,,fix(util): Handle 'Finding sources' messages in RemoteProgress,closed,False,282,"When running a long running operation (such as a clone on a large repo),
Git may return a message indicating that it is 'Finding sources'. Since
there is no bit field value for this message, this causes a large amount
of error messages to be emitted to stderr.

This patch fixes this by adding another bit field value for this
message, FINDING_SOURCES. Derived classes can look for this op_code and
handle it appropriately.",https://api.github.com/repos/gitpython-developers/GitPython/issues/282,2015-04-16T07:13:26Z,2015-04-16T07:13:26Z,2015-04-16T07:13:26Z,2,4,2,1,[],[],[],[],Byron,63622.0,User,False,[],https://github.com/gitpython-developers/GitPython/pull/282.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/gitpython-developers/GitPython/pulls/282/commits,010,"['f9e7a3d93da741f81a5af2e84422376c54f1f337', '6d83f44007c5c581eae7ddc6c5de33311b7c1895']"
