10692,PullRequestEvent,2017-04-28 21:18:16+00:00,30509483,clab/dynet,398875,neubig,2374376.0,clab,118231627,,Add broadcasting along the batch dimension to pick (python pick_batch),closed,False,497,Addresses #493 ,https://api.github.com/repos/clab/dynet/issues/497,2017-04-28T21:18:16Z,2017-04-28T21:18:16Z,2017-04-28T21:18:16Z,1,29,3,3,[],[],[],[],neubig,398875.0,User,False,[],https://github.com/clab/dynet/pull/497.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/clab/dynet/pulls/497/commits,010,[]
10700,PullRequestEvent,2017-11-06 11:29:17+00:00,30509483,clab/dynet,398875,neubig,2374376.0,clab,142717938,,Some partial supports for READ-only inplaced operations.,open,False,929,"This PR adds certain partial enhancements for READ-only in-place operations, replacing another PR #840 which brings too much complexities and might bother the users.

The concerned Nodes are the ones which can safely reuse memories (no rewriting for forward values):
Reshape(forward/backward), Identity(forward/backward), NoBackprop(forward-only), FlipGradient(forward-only).

Some notes:
1. Since `NoBackprop` and `FlipGradient` need special gradient manipulation, they have their own backward memories.
2. For auto-batch mode, currently simply forbid batching for thoes nodes. Firstly the memory-allocation part of auto-batching seems a little complex for me, so I do not change much there in the fear of breaking sth; Secondly, in auto-batching mode, maybe memory is even less important.
3. (TODO) For the memory saving of WRITE nodes, we might need some better mechanism for them.

* In fact, I'm not quite sure about the dealing of the pointers in the ExecutionEngines when doing memory allocating or sharing, wonder if they are appropriate. (Although all the tests have been passed)
