10734,PullRequestEvent,2015-03-31 22:08:31+00:00,6248645,ARM-DOE/pyart,7915525,gamaanderson,2540600.0,ARM-DOE,32324841,,Fast grid mapper,closed,False,265,"This is a different version of map_to_grid made to be as fast as possible. It works like TITAN, that is, instead of pushing radar points to Cartesian and then interpolate a cloud of points it search for points in the radar coordinates. This has some limitation but it makes 1 millions grid points in 1.3s. It still only with nearest_point interpolation, but one could add multi-linear. I needed to use a lot of Cython to get that velocity and that make me think how much a full Cython version of the original map_to_grid could make.

P.S. to call it use map.grid_from_radars(radars, grid_shape, grid_limits ,grid_mapping_func='fast_map_to_grid' ,fields=[...])",https://api.github.com/repos/ARM-DOE/pyart/issues/265,,2015-03-31T22:08:30Z,2015-03-31T22:08:30Z,5,20929,5,6,[],[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/ARM-DOE/pyart/pull/265.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/ARM-DOE/pyart/pulls/265/commits,010,"['27ebda02fa90b7415b40b61d73743023a855235e', 'c3b30f2cb4e158e2f80b121689b17807d9a40f85', '5c5b44fea27e4821fdfd08e3a671cc9a33b0c23d', '6c00278816a86a5983e000e54ced5b453c5298a3', '258c1cac9e60c6c3688f888de48de1a768b09ab2', 'c631475a43b009302d57fa40363119a6e7ac4292', 'fc7e31ef95e1fca3d09f83a39dc58132d12f494e', 'd4a4a09f09727b517daac4caf948976b403df227', '84c55f2cb3f69e8123fc13dbd9f7d6a78f814091', 'f8870f72bb6ae6af6e134a0f9afaee92e0d81959', 'a52a5ed5d3305badcb7b58ab43a031151c22770e', 'f1f19cdae189b6b400871a49b9b377fabbce58c0', '1ee64bc261dbe03071ddf2b0eb32d1b13afaa20d']"
