10797,PullRequestEvent,2015-05-12 22:06:44+00:00,24213271,adobe-type-tools/afdko,2856984,readroberts,2768660.0,adobe-type-tools,35071523,,[tx] make temporary files in the user's %TMP% folder on Windows,closed,False,51,"as noted here (https://github.com/adobe-type-tools/afdko/issues/20), on Windows the stdio.h tmpfile function tries to create temporary files in the root folder, thus requiring adminstrative privileges.

I only patched the tx command, but I know the same issue affects all the afdko commands which use tmpfile.

Anyway, here is my workaround. Maybe somebody could help me find a better place for this code, so that it can be reused in other parts of the library...

thank you,

C.",https://api.github.com/repos/adobe-type-tools/afdko/issues/51,2015-05-12T22:06:43Z,2015-05-12T22:06:43Z,2015-05-12T22:06:43Z,1,33,3,1,[],[],[],[],readroberts,2856984.0,User,False,[],https://github.com/adobe-type-tools/afdko/pull/51.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/adobe-type-tools/afdko/pulls/51/commits,010,['d270471a6028619bd9f50c0c382e69dc6feef4fe']
