11410,PullRequestEvent,2018-03-21 01:06:40+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,12532471,CMLivingston,3065172.0,pantsbuild,176362280,,Resolve for current platform only if resolving a local python dist with native extensions,open,False,5618,"### Problem

If a pants.ini files specifies default platforms that include more than just the current platform, local python dist targets will fail to resolve during the resolve requirements task because they are build locally for the current platform. Furthermore, the resolve requirements task does not plumb binary target platform arguments through at resolve time, so we need a mechanism to check if there are native sources in a python dist in play, and pass only ""current"" to the pex resolver if this is the case.

### Solution

Check if a python_dist target is in play during requirements resolution and if any of these targets contain native (c or cpp) sources. If they do, set the platforms parameter of the pex resolver to contain only ""current"". 

### Result

Pants projects that have pants.ini files which specify multiple default platforms can now build local python dist targets for the current platform only.",https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/issues/5618,,,2018-03-21T01:06:39Z,1,17,2,2,CONTRIBUTOR,[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/pull/5618.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/pulls/5618/commits,010,"['448bd4fd59582a0681e13faa3d8f598e86761ee2', '9953176cff497dee14a69a1088741849d6d854a5', '041fd0145b765578839c99134a4cf70500355aa3', 'fe9dc41efa50c186511da0122bcba25310523570', '56a2c5ccb2c6bbcdab473944a00b0bf2e79c6c2d', 'e9efdce66c3d3da3dcd9a3caec5f5bc4f4ec8366', '7a90d774368be7d7f3a3c854466c9d3cb5c63f80', '9b1be1b29705eb3874e55877a12537752db6e931', 'c2afc3a8ae5c0e3a0057655423dce4db73fdc61b', '9ded26d1439ada7287d8f2b8c94ed1e00c99efd8', 'afa2a28c0bef6314781e0b127169e2bef59953f6']"
