12015,PullRequestEvent,2015-06-05 09:56:16+00:00,12407457,Exa-Networks/exabgp,6838824,tmmorin,5339170.0,Exa-Networks,36944844,,Fix encoding/decoding of transitive bit in extended communities,closed,False,286,"There is a trick: bit set means ""not transitive"".

RFC4360:
        T - Transitive bit
            Value 0: The community is transitive across ASes
            Value 1: The community is non-transitive across ASes

(This was found, and the fix confirmed, by interop testing with Contrail BGP implementation.)

