12023,PullRequestEvent,2017-05-09 04:30:03+00:00,12407457,Exa-Networks/exabgp,2599281,ruissalo,5339170.0,Exa-Networks,119581588,,Add Segment Routing IS-IS BGP-LS extensions,open,False,615,"@thomas-mangin I'm creating a PR so you can take a look before merging. It shouldn't break anything. I also added a packet hex dump to the qa/tests for these changes.

This PR contains IS-IS segment routing extensions to BGP-LS (draft-gredler-idr-bgp-ls-segment-routing-ext-03).
Added TLVs mostly correspond to those currently implemented by IOS-XR 6.1.1.  Binding SIDs extensions are not included but I don't think Cisco supports them at the moment.

Use Case: Segment IDs are learned via ExaBGP/BGP-LS (with SR extensions enabled) => controller application computes the constrained LSP using the segment IDs previously learned => LSP is programmed via ExaBGP/BGP-LU session.

I'll update the wiki with a blog post on how ExaBGP can be used as an SDN controller to program LSPs using segment routing instructions.
",https://api.github.com/repos/Exa-Networks/exabgp/issues/615,,,2017-05-09T04:30:02Z,3,647,116,21,[],[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/Exa-Networks/exabgp/pull/615.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/Exa-Networks/exabgp/pulls/615/commits,010,"['192637e19f09c44f315158e174e5925ffa2518d7', 'd299cc90f6cfe9d9db93f48320b837af7bd41010', 'd5636c963c1e1e95f0ca98f1e8373ee56d3bf7f8', '06d6c107a7860d1ac99ecfb68f3786dd73d6aeb7', '34ee55d9e8a22e79ec4c679d1e9f237f530f79c1']"
