12320,PullRequestEvent,2016-11-25 21:57:07+00:00,13512018,python-diamond/Diamond,65675,josegonzalez,5668086.0,python-diamond,57672687,,Allow SNMP collector to address different communities,closed,False,386,"The SNMP collector uses the constant string 'agent' as the index for its CommunityData object.  This means multiple SNMP collectors will conflict, as second and subsequent collectors will use the same community name as the first collector, even if the diamond configuration specifies a different community.

