12327,PullRequestEvent,2015-11-05 10:54:07+00:00,13512018,python-diamond/Diamond,7429716,ggs-sglimm,5668086.0,python-diamond,49808496,,Rate-limit reconnections,open,False,320,"Hi,

we found that the GraphiteHandler (possibly others, too) can create quite a high network load, when the Carbon endpoint is down.

The current implementation tries to reconnect on every incoming metric. This causes both a TCP reconnection and (if no local DNS cache is used) a DNS query. This merge request rate limits the GraphiteHandler to once per 10 seconds (configurable).",https://api.github.com/repos/python-diamond/Diamond/issues/320,,,2015-11-05T10:54:07Z,1,15,6,1,[],[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/python-diamond/Diamond/pull/320.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/python-diamond/Diamond/pulls/320/commits,010,['e0b942d515fd16a9b12d8cf78813fc56203dca56']
