12556,PullRequestEvent,2016-10-14 18:35:42+00:00,53438969,globus/globus-cli,3958448,corpulentcoffee,6120321.0,globus,89433215,,Fix non-batch globus transfer async-delete --path,open,False,48,"On the current release, `globus transfer async-delete --path=xxx` does not work, and instead behaves as if the user did `--batch`.

Adjusts the check to be just `if batch` rather than `if batch is not None` since `batch` will be either `True` or `False`, not `None`. This is consistent with the guard check for `batch` at the top of this command's implementation, which is just a truthy/falsey check.",https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-cli/issues/48,,,2016-10-14T18:35:42Z,1,1,1,1,[],[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/globus/globus-cli/pull/48.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-cli/pulls/48/commits,010,['96930cc7d3d4fda009c01d7732a06b61809df08b']
