12655,PullRequestEvent,2018-07-12 01:12:14+00:00,77478378,ethereum/py-evm,205327,carver,6250754.0,ethereum,200864428,MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MjAwODY0NDI4,WIP: starting in on peer performance tracking,open,False,1009,"### What was wrong?

Fixes #868 

### How was it fixed?

(planned)
- track throughput performance of peers (and maybe latency separately)
- favor high-throughput peers, sending them bigger requests
- if performance of a peer is bad enough, we will eventually not request anything from them (this happens naturally in the current approach, but we might add a feature to be a little more aggressive about stopping contact with slow peers)

Tests are failing, but I have to stop for the night. I haven't had a chance to look at why they fail.

