12990,PullRequestEvent,2017-10-04 19:56:58+00:00,9801644,elastic/elasticsearch-py,146550,fxdgear,6764390.0,elastic,91029051,,allow to set a specific CA directory through ca_cert_dir option,closed,False,471,"I am having a problem setting up the authentication using host certificate, because I can not specify a directory path to the CA certificates. What I wanted to have:

``` pyhton
cl = Elasticsearch('https:', verify_certs=True,ca_cert_dir='/opt/xxx/yyyy/security/certificates/')
```

I know I can create a file which contains all CAs in /opt/xxx/yyyy/security/certificates/ directory, but this means I have to maintain this file always. 
I exposed the ca_cert_dir option and it works well. Could you please include to the next release?
Thanks,
Zoltan
