13035,PullRequestEvent,2017-05-05 18:15:23+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,386473,devigned,6844498.0,Azure,118670973,,Add support for Azure CDN,closed,False,3147,"Adds support for Azure CDN including, profiles, endpoints, origins, edge nodes and custom domains.

---

This checklist is used to make sure that common guidelines for a pull request are followed.

### General Guidelines

- [x] The PR has modified HISTORY.rst with an appropriate description of the change (see [Modifying change log](https://github.com/Azure/azure-cli/tree/master/doc/authoring_command_modules#modify-change-log)).

### Command Guidelines

- [x] Each command and parameter has a meaningful description.
- [x] Each new command has a test.

(see [Authoring Command Modules](https://github.com/Azure/azure-cli/tree/master/doc/authoring_command_modules))

```
$ az cdn -h

Group
    az cdn: Manage Azure Content Delivery Networks (CDN).

Commands:
    custom-domain: Manage Azure CDN Custom Domains to provide custom host names for Endpoints.
    edge-node    : View all available edge nodes.
    endpoint     : Manage Azure CDN Endpoints which define the hostname and endpoints.
    name-exists  : Check the availability of a resource name.
    origin       : List or show existing origins related to CDN endpoints.
    profile      : Manage Azure CDN Profiles which define which CDN provider for your edge network.
    usage        : Check the quota and actual usage of the CDN profiles under the given
                   subscription.
```

```
$ az cdn profile -h

Group
    az cdn profile

Commands:
    create: Creates a new CDN profile with a profile name under the specified resource group.
    delete: Deletes an existing CDN profile with the specified parameters.
    list  : List your Azure Content Delivery Network (CDN) profiles.
    show  : Gets a CDN profile with the specified profile name under the specified subscription and
            resource group.
    update: Updates a CDN profile with a profile name under the specified resource group.
    usage : Checks the quota and actual usage of endpoints under the given CDN profile.
```

```
$ az cdn profile create -h

Command
    az cdn profile create: Creates a new CDN profile with a profile name under the specified
    resource group.

Arguments
    --name -n           [Required]: The name of the CDN profile.
    --resource-group -g [Required]: Name of resource group. You can configure the default group
                                    using `az configure --defaults group=<name>`.
    --location -l                 : Location. You can configure the default location using `az
                                    configure --defaults location=<location>`.
    --sku                         : The pricing tier (defines a CDN provider, feature list and rate)
                                    of the CDN profile. Defaults to Standard_Akamai.  Allowed
                                    values: Custom_Verizon, Premium_Verizon, Standard_Akamai,
                                    Standard_ChinaCdn, Standard_Verizon.  Default: Standard_Akamai.
    --tags                        : Space separated tags in 'key[=value]' format. Use '' to clear
                                    existing tags.

Global Arguments
    --debug                       : Increase logging verbosity to show all debug logs.
    --help -h                     : Show this help message and exit.
    --output -o                   : Output format.  Allowed values: json, jsonc, table, tsv.
                                    Default: json.
    --query                       : JMESPath query string. See http://jmespath.org/ for more
                                    information and examples.
    --verbose                     : Increase logging verbosity. Use --debug for full debug logs.

Examples
    Create a CDN profile using Verizon premium CDN
        az cdn profile create -g group -n profile --sku Premium_Verizon
```

```
$ az cdn endpoint -h

Group
    az cdn endpoint

Commands:
    create                : CDN endpoint is the entity within a CDN profile containing configuration
                            information such as origin, protocol, content caching and delivery
                            behavior.
    delete                : Deletes an existing CDN endpoint with the specified endpoint name under
                            the specified subscription, resource group and profile.
    list                  : Lists existing CDN endpoints.
    load                  : Pre-loads a content to CDN.
    purge                 : Removes a content from CDN.
    show                  : Gets an existing CDN endpoint with the specified endpoint name under the
                            specified subscription, resource group and profile.
    start                 : Starts an existing CDN endpoint that is on a stopped state.
    stop                  : Stops an existing running CDN endpoint.
    update                : Updates a CDN endpoint within a profile and resource group.
    validate-custom-domain: Validates the custom domain mapping to ensure it maps to the correct CDN
                            endpoint in DNS.
```

```
$ az cdn endpoint create -h

Command
    az cdn endpoint create: CDN endpoint is the entity within a CDN profile containing configuration
    information such as origin, protocol, content caching and delivery behavior.

Arguments
    --name -n           [Required]
    --origin            [Required]: Endpoint origin specified by the following space delimited 3
                                    tuple: `www.example.com http_port https_port`. The HTTP and
                                    HTTPs ports are optional and will default to 80 and 443
                                    respectively.
    --profile-name      [Required]
    --resource-group -g [Required]: Name of resource group. You can configure the default group
                                    using `az configure --defaults group=<name>`.
    --content-types-to-compress   : List of content types on which compression applies. The value
                                    should be a valid MIME type.
    --enable-compression          : If compression is enabled, content will be served as compressed
                                    if user requests for a compressed version. Content won't be
                                    compressed on CDN when requested content is smaller than 1 byte
                                    or larger than 1 MB.  Allowed values: false, true.
    --location -l                 : Location. You can configure the default location using `az
                                    configure --defaults location=<location>`.
    --no-http                     : Indicates whether HTTP traffic is not allowed on the endpoint.
                                    Default is to allow HTTP traffic.  Allowed values: false, true.
    --no-https                    : Indicates whether HTTPS traffic is not allowed on the endpoint.
                                    Default is to allow HTTPS traffic.  Allowed values: false, true.
    --origin-host-header          : The host header CDN sends along with content requests to origin.
                                    The default value is the host name of the origin.
    --origin-path                 : The path used when CDN sends request to origin.
    --query-string-caching        : Defines the query string caching behavior.  Allowed values:
                                    BypassCaching, IgnoreQueryString, NotSet, UseQueryString.
                                    Default: IgnoreQueryString.
    --tags                        : Space separated tags in 'key[=value]' format. Use '' to clear
                                    existing tags.

Global Arguments
    --debug                       : Increase logging verbosity to show all debug logs.
    --help -h                     : Show this help message and exit.
    --output -o                   : Output format.  Allowed values: json, jsonc, table, tsv.
                                    Default: json.
    --query                       : JMESPath query string. See http://jmespath.org/ for more
                                    information and examples.
    --verbose                     : Increase logging verbosity. Use --debug for full debug logs.

Examples
    Create an endpoint with a custom domain origin
        az cdn endpoint create -g group -n endpoint --profile-name profile \
            --origin www.example.com


    Create an endpoint with a custom domain origin with HTTP and HTTPS ports
        az cdn endpoint create -g group -n endpoint --profile-name profile \
            --origin www.example.com 88 4444


    Create an endpoint with a custom domain with compression and only HTTPS
        az cdn endpoint create -g group -n endpoint --profile-name profile \
            --origin www.example.com --no-http --enable-compression
```

```
$ az cdn origin -h

Group
    az cdn origin

Commands:
    list: Lists all of the existing origins within an endpoint.
    show: Gets an existing origin within an endpoint.
```

```
$ az cdn custom-domain -h

Group
    az cdn custom-domain

Commands:
    create: Creates a new custom domain within an endpoint.
    delete: Deletes an existing custom domain within an endpoint.
    list  : Lists all of the existing custom domains within an endpoint.
    show  : Gets an exisitng custom domain within an endpoint.
```",https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/issues/3147,2017-05-05T18:15:23Z,2017-05-05T18:15:23Z,2017-05-05T18:15:23Z,20,5829,5,36,[],[],[],[],devigned,386473.0,User,False,[],https://github.com/Azure/azure-cli/pull/3147.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/pulls/3147/commits,010,"['7a56d053aefec4006e54372ada887b6085e70a64', '4815718f026b4ac6b67576eac73b150b181eda53', '537e175ac0a7fd762a83567f42ebe7eed2f3033d', 'b823f5333764e78d8e65060e9515df1c47e8263e', 'f16cddd58c686095e005efef07da8d03b0292337', '343bae964c6dbe1fd6907e9d39ac1e027b6ce6e4', '3214890a14e439fea2616d558dcc823ce0cbc59d', '9e8196c6844acec003b6232d0e293d98bb1b79dc', '74a1e4917e2f8ac6a818dabddc7fdc0a05f4977e', '23790d8326739f53ccd750b18e40a9ce610c9767', 'a5fc42a352adff3fbb618f6558cda101ed201087', '5531078d5ccff3765847219612d5e7e4dce622eb', 'e3482cba8a73cd22d2314c0893ec341eded3cc7a', 'e26026c4c2348efabd49c9b20ef9664ade92f30b', 'bc818e480eaa7a858879cd8513c69482566f2e09', '885bf6d4cbcc542d5849df18c1ba82892bb18a84', '295188c78ebd4ed39c718caf2f56df45748f5fed', '6bb40aa160502958cce6f54a9914f2ef47227ec4', '8e986d28f00a41b06b6dbf77a8c59d679a5969a9', 'c30d5e337cafa4194959ca44b52998c19e686159']"
