14217,PullRequestEvent,2017-09-12 20:53:37+00:00,34739117,pytest-dev/pluggy,1085180,nicoddemus,8897583.0,pytest-dev,140680431,,Re-add _Result.result as an attr which triggers a deprecation warning,open,False,88,"This should fix the `pluggymaster` environment in pytest.

Guys I was wondering if it wouldn't be better instead of `get_result()` to have `result` as a read-only property, with the same semantics as `get_result()`? 

`outcome.result` is more user-friendly than `outcome.get_result()`. It seems we are not using one of the key benefits of properties of being able to change an attribute access into a property at some later time without breaking users.",https://api.github.com/repos/pytest-dev/pluggy/issues/88,,,2017-09-12T20:53:37Z,1,17,2,2,OWNER,[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/pytest-dev/pluggy/pull/88.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/pytest-dev/pluggy/pulls/88/commits,010,"['8b9fd3a432d65f3b85066c21abe8af785315e5cf', '0d5fd6a4119e5a3c8a2e54d7b9b87349835dd357']"
