15480,PullRequestEvent,2015-09-19 20:21:58+00:00,1750874,django-money/django-money,374612,benjaoming,12234694.0,django-money,9549339,,Implement support for user-set defaults.,closed,False,44,"For everyone who has ever had to work with models like this:

```
class Foo(models.Model)
    field1 = MoneyField(max_digits=12, decimal_places=2, default_currency=settings.DEFAULT_CURRENCY)
    field2 = MoneyField(max_digits=12, decimal_places=2, default_currency=settings.DEFAULT_CURRENCY)
    ...
    fieldN = MoneyField(max_digits=12, decimal_places=2, default_currency=settings.DEFAULT_CURRENCY)
```

I submit a humble pull request which allows you to set defaults for `max_digits`, `decimal_places`, and `default_currency` using the variables `MONEYFIELD_MAX_DIGITS`, `MONEYFIELD_DECIMAL_PLACES` and `MONEYFIELD_DEFAULT_CURRENCY` in `settings.py`.

If you see anything about my code that's worth pointing out - feel free to let me know. Cheers (:",https://api.github.com/repos/django-money/django-money/issues/44,,2015-09-19T20:21:58Z,2015-09-19T20:21:58Z,2,18,6,1,[],[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/django-money/django-money/pull/44.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/django-money/django-money/pulls/44/commits,010,"['405af51f86c1707e92f4cd3eb97431966afe387f', '6d7615802c1dec476f0a7c621e8a99e28956c7fb']"
