15516,PullRequestEvent,2016-08-15 20:02:02+00:00,42593972,b12io/orchestra,57725,marcua,12401025.0,b12io,81294793,,JS linting and building,closed,False,353,"I read a bit of the JS front-end codebase and noticed a few inconsistencies, then I noticed the gulp linting pipeline wasn't checking anything because it lacked proper configuration. I went for the angular code style, it's very close to the existing JS code and didn't require many changes for the JS linting step to pass.

* a33b3e9: gulp global installation takes a while and there is no reason to reinstall it at
every gulp build
* 2bf4083: By default jscs doesn't enforce anything. Add a `.jscsrc` based on the [angular
