16184,PullRequestEvent,2017-10-02 20:11:22+00:00,43023379,hackingmaterials/atomate,16827130,shyamd,14116185.0,hackingmaterials,144272256,,New optimization,open,False,162,"Updating the optimization per #19 

Switched ediffg to default to -0.05
changed default to not include MaxForceErrorHandler 
add in half_kpts_first_relax and set to default to true

Currently, we use double relaxations. Would it make sense to switch to full opt since that enables the 2% vol change check @shyuep recommends? Does this primarily mitigate issues with Pulay stresses?

In reference to @montoyjh's suggestion of looking into the FFT  grid size, I ran some test calculations of GGA+U and SCAN optimizations for Si, Fe, Al2O3, Fe2O3, and GaN after rattling all atoms + one significant perturbation. In all cases setting ENAUG to 4*ENCUT was as at minimum 7% faster average over 4 tries, and in some cases as much as 54% faster. The resulting structures and energies all matched with the expected values from MP, or in the case of SCAN were self-consistent. The benefit seems to scale with the complexity of the calculation, more atoms = bigger speedup. ",https://api.github.com/repos/hackingmaterials/atomate/issues/162,,,2017-10-02T20:11:22Z,6,12,9,2,CONTRIBUTOR,[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/hackingmaterials/atomate/pull/162.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/hackingmaterials/atomate/pulls/162/commits,010,[]
16187,PullRequestEvent,2018-06-25 16:59:32+00:00,43091756,hackingmaterials/matminer,20934665,ldwillia,14116185.0,hackingmaterials,197176734,MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MTk3MTc2NzM0,Bugfix of lambdas in GRDF's and AFS's presets in site.py,open,False,260,"Updated lambda functions for GeneralizedRadialDistributionFunction.from_preset and AngularFourierSeries.from_preset to use a local variable instead of grabbing an outer scope variable when defining lambda functions in a loop. Previous behavior caused all bins to be identical and using the final value of 'center' instead of creating a series. Also updated default values in GeneralizedRadialDistributionFunction.from_preset from width=0.5, spacing=0.5 to width=1.0, spacing=1.0 in order to avoid error: ""ValueError: Numerical integration does not play well with the chosen bin functionals, choose new ones.""

## Summary

* Fixed lambda functions in GRDF and AFS .from_preset methods
* updated default width and spacing in GRDF.from_preset to avoid error
* Added self to implementors list for GRDF and AFS (Is that okay? If not, remove.)

## TODO (if any)

* GRDF.from_preset('histogram') sometimes produces a value of 'inf' for some bins. Cause currently unknown.",https://api.github.com/repos/hackingmaterials/matminer/issues/260,,,2018-06-25T16:59:31Z,1,7,7,1,NONE,[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/hackingmaterials/matminer/pull/260.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/hackingmaterials/matminer/pulls/260/commits,010,['f480d3fc23d8d80a77527c9c3434baff33d3a219']
