16226,PullRequestEvent,2015-11-30 16:00:09+00:00,43852872,PulpQE/pulp-smash,7295540,peterlacko,14839747.0,PulpQE,52141996,,Puppet tests for syncing and publishing with puppet_distributor,open,False,45,"PR contains tests for following functionality:
* It is possible to create two puppet repos, with and without feed URLs respectively (CreateTestCase),
* Create repo with valid feed and run sync ends without errors (SyncValidFeedTestCase),
* Create repo with invalid feed and run sync ends with error (SyncInvalidFeedTestCase),
* Following steps finish without errors (PublishTestCase)
  * Create two repositories: `foo` and `bar`.
  * upload custom puppet module to `foo`,
  * copy `foo` to `bar` and publish both,
  * download modules from their expected locations on pulp server file system,
  * verify module integrity",https://api.github.com/repos/PulpQE/pulp-smash/issues/45,,,2015-11-30T16:00:09Z,1,649,0,3,[],[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/PulpQE/pulp-smash/pull/45.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/PulpQE/pulp-smash/pulls/45/commits,010,['88c14461a1f9f9736edfc446112eb38e982c2f8f']
