17702,PullRequestEvent,2017-08-14 06:39:38+00:00,71932349,ray-project/ray,113316,pcmoritz,22125274.0,ray-project,135505421,,Fix bugs in task timeline visualization.,closed,False,836,"This fixes #835, and the following problems.

- `total_info` was defined twice and all of the fields added initially were overwritten by the line `total_info = copy.copy(task_spec)`.
- When we modified `task_spec[""Args""]` by converting object IDs to hex (for displaying when the tasks were clicked on), we modified the args in place, so that when we later produced the arrows, all object IDs were hex strings and not object IDs.
- When we drew the arrows, we were incorrectly handling object IDs versus other types of arguments.

cc @alanamarzoev ",https://api.github.com/repos/ray-project/ray/issues/836,2017-08-14T06:39:38Z,2017-08-14T06:39:38Z,2017-08-14T06:39:38Z,3,68,66,1,[],[],[],[],pcmoritz,113316.0,User,False,[],https://github.com/ray-project/ray/pull/836.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/ray-project/ray/pulls/836/commits,010,"['3e3e950d33712d8f17110e9f70cc6385b140a36f', '74e546c4688382e89920bfc5d375a43614d01f7d', '9d07bb3cdc66a0cadc95acc7ac372dd4bec9a103']"
17706,PullRequestEvent,2018-03-12 23:43:53+00:00,71932349,ray-project/ray,4802083,barrachri,22125274.0,ray-project,174524073,,WIP: Add external module as a node scaler.,open,False,1703,"<!--
Thank you for your contribution!

Please review https://github.com/ray-project/ray/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.rst before opening a pull request.
-->

## What do these changes do?
These changes add the possibility to specify an external module as autoscaler.

```yaml
provider:
    type: external
    module: this.is.my.module
```

`module` will be loaded and used a nodescaler.

More about the origin of this PR [here](https://groups.google.com/forum/?utm_medium=email&utm_source=footer#!msg/ray-dev/uhtE5D05Q5s/jcLut7GeBgAJ).
<!-- Please give a short brief about these changes. -->

## Related issue number

<!-- Are there any issues opened that will be resolved by merging this change? -->
