18048,PullRequestEvent,2017-11-13 01:21:42+00:00,79083614,python-trio/trio,609896,njsmith,26335827.0,python-trio,152135917,,Make measure_backlog more robust against weird errors,open,False,349,"@nmalaguti is reporting that on a particular VPS they have access to,
sometimes, the test_open_tcp_listeners_backlog test is blowing up with
EMFILE and breaking other tests. It seems to involve the kernel
switching to using syn cookies, and then suddenly infinitely many
connection attempts can appear to succeed.

A real fix would be to make the test robust against syncookies, but
I'm not yet sure how to do that. In the mean time this at least should
make the test more robustly clean up after itself, so that this causes
a well-defined failure without shrapnel flying out to hit other tests.",https://api.github.com/repos/python-trio/trio/issues/349,,,2017-11-13T01:21:41Z,1,13,13,1,OWNER,[],[],[],,,,,[],https://github.com/python-trio/trio/pull/349.patch,https://api.github.com/repos/python-trio/trio/pulls/349/commits,010,['80357fc288f70fa9c053e928bf81e498ff41b078']
